@startuml
autonumber
skinparam maxMessageSize 250

box "Orchestration Layer" #LightCyan
participant "Camunda Engine" as Camunda
participant "Kong Gateway" as Kong
end box

box "Microservice Layer" #LightYellow
participant "Prosumer MS" as ProsumerMS
participant "Utility Operator MS" as UtilityMS
participant "Telemetry MS" as TelemetryMS
participant "Flexibility Forecasting MS" as ForecastMS
end box

box "AI Layer" #LightBlue
participant "Ollama Server\n(EC2 - LLM)" as Ollama
end box

box "Persistence Layer" #LightGreen
database "AWS RDS" as DB
end box

== Data Gathering Phase (Orchestrated by Camunda) ==

Camunda -> Kong: GET /Prosumers (Fetch Prosumers & Assets)
Kong -> ProsumerMS: Forward Request
ProsumerMS -> DB: JDBC SELECT Prosumers and Assets
DB --> ProsumerMS: Results
ProsumerMS --> Kong: 200 OK\n{Prosumers[], Assets[]}
Kong --> Camunda: Prosumer Data Context

Camunda -> Kong: GET /UtilityOperators/GridCells (Fetch Zones)
Kong -> UtilityMS: Forward Request
UtilityMS -> DB: JDBC SELECT Grid Cells
DB --> UtilityMS: Results
UtilityMS --> Kong: 200 OK {GridCells[]}
Kong --> Camunda: Grid Zone Context

Camunda -> Kong: GET /Telemetry (Fetch recent metrics)
Kong -> TelemetryMS: Forward Request
TelemetryMS -> DB: JDBC SELECT latest Telemetry
DB --> TelemetryMS: Results
TelemetryMS --> Kong: 200 OK {TelemetryRecords[]}
Kong --> Camunda: Telemetry Context

note right
  Camunda aggregates Prosumer, Grid, Telemetry,
  Flexibility Events, and Recommendations 
  into the **ForecastRequest** DTO.
end note

== Flexibility Forecasting Phase (AI Analysis) ==
Camunda -> Kong: POST /FlexibilityForecasting/analyze\n{ForecastRequest}

note right
  **Payload: ForecastRequest** {
    "analysisType": "...",
    "eventType": "DISCHARGE",
    "assetId": 12345,
    "recommendedAction": "...",
    "events": [ ... ],
    "recommendations": [ ... ] }
end note
Kong -> ForecastMS: Forward POST /FlexibilityForecasting/analyze

ForecastMS -> Kong: REST POST /api/generate\n{Compiled context from ForecastRequest}
Kong -> Ollama: Forward POST /api/generate

note right : Goal: Analyze the provided historical events,\ntelemetry context, and recommendations\nfrom the ForecastRequest to determine the\nsentiment and success rate (e.g., if the\npast "Discharge" commands actually resulted\nin a "Grid Stable" state).
Ollama -> Ollama: Compute Sentiment \n& Success Rate
Ollama --> Kong: 200 OK {sentiment: "Positive", successProbability: 0.85}
Kong --> ForecastMS: 200 OK {sentiment, successProbability}

ForecastMS -> DB: JDBC INSERT INTO FlexibilityForecast\n(analysisType, sentiment, successProbability)
DB --> ForecastMS: 201 Created

ForecastMS --> Kong: 200 OK {ForecastResult}
Kong --> Camunda: Forecasting Complete & Results Received
@enduml